description:
&lt;p&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse Blackthorn Ward Care of the Elderly&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are friendly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are welcoming&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are a community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Join the Whipps Cross family and be a part of an amazing team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have fantastic opportunities available for you to join our nursing teams. We are looking for passionate Band 5 registered nurses with excellent communication skills who understand the importance of patient care and have the ability to assess, plan, implement and evaluate a care plan, recognising the specific needs of patients and relatives with compassion and empathy. Maintaining high standards of nursing you will be a team player who enjoys an unpredictable working day with the desire to drive change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide you with excellent development opportunities and a team that lives and works by our WeCare values which are at the heart of everything that we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported in your nursing career where we will provide you with the following development opportunities such as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fundamental of Care for Nursing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career clinics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rotations within directorates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated practice development nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capital Nurse Programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Individualised personal development plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are committed and would like to develop your skills further why not apply online for a post via our open day where you will be given the opportunity to learn about our services and be interviewed by our senior nurses. If you are successful, we will offer you a post on the day. All nurses are required to pass the medicines management test before the interview&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Care Quality Commission has recognised the significant improvements made at Whipps Cross in their latest visit and the 2018 Staff Survey results showed staff have seen many improvements in their working lives. With our passionate staff and commitment to safe and compassionate care, we know Whipps Cross will keep getting better and better. We’d love you to join us on our journey to good and outstanding. Come and be part of the Whipps Cross family where you can make a difference.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ilene Paglinawan, Matron on i.paglinawan@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
